[3] Cook Islands
Date: 31 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Radio New Zealand [edited]
<http://www.radionz.co.nz/news/latest/200610310604/dengue_fever_outbreak_reported_in_cook_islands>

There have been around 170 cases of dengue fever in the past few
months in the Cook Islands, although no New Zealand tourists to the
country are known to have contracted the disease. The outbreak was
first noticed in May this year [2006], and has mostly affected the
main island of Rarotonga.
The clinical director at Rarotonga Hospital says most of the cases
have been mild. Dr Henry Tikaka says he cannot tell how bad the
outbreak will get, but he says for this time of year there are a high
number of cases. Dr Tikaka says people are being advised to clear
away any mosquito breeding grounds.
Visitors to the country are being told to bring extra insect repellent.
--
