[4] French Polynesia
Date: 2 Nov 2006
From:Pablo Nart <pablo.nart@terra.es>
Source: ABC Radio Australia, 02 Nov 2006, 18:05:15 [edited]
<http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/news/stories/s1779899.htm>

A taskforce will meet in French Polynesia this week to discuss an
outbreak of dengue fever which has affected close to 400 people.
In the last week of October [2006], 37 new cases of dengue fever were
reported, bringing the total of new cases to 129 for the month.
French Polynesia's ministry of health says the number of confirmed
cases over the past 5 months has now reached 376.
The most affected areas are the capital Papeete, but also towns in
the outskirts, where the international airport is located.
--
