[5] Nepal
Date: 1 Nov 2006
From: Patricia Doyle <dr_p_doyle@hotmail.com>
Source: Times of India [edited]
<http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/275798.cms>

9 persons have been hospitalised after showing symptoms of dengue in
Nepalgunj district of Nepal, a report said on Wednesday.
Of the 9 patients who showed symptoms of the disease, 7 have been
discharged after treatment, the National News Agency (RSS) reported;
2 are still undergoing treatment in a hospital.
Nepal has arranged dengue testing and treatment facilities in
different hospitals in the Capital Kathmandu and along its border
with India following the outbreak of dengue in the neighbouring country.
--
