[6] India - Delhi and other states
Date: 2 Nov 2006
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Press Information Bureau [Government of India](press
release), New Delhi, India, 2 Nov 2006 [edited]
<http://pib.nic.in/release/release.asp?relid=21700>

A total of 9161 cases and 152 deaths have been reported from India as
a whole including Delhi as of 2 Nov 2006 up to 12.30 hrs [local time].
A total number of 2775 cases and 55 deaths have been reported from
Delhi, NCR and other States. Out of these, 1718 cases have been
reported from Delhi, while 1057 cases are from the NCR and other
states. The 1057cases from outside Delhi includes 327 cases from
Haryana, 570 cases from Uttar Pradesh, 22 cases from Rajasthan and
138 from others.
Apart from Delhi the maximum number of dengue cases have been
reported from Rajasthan (1224) followed by Kerala (849), West Bengal
(820), Punjab (809), Uttar Pradesh (604), Maharashtra (582), Gujarat
(475), Haryana (395),Tamil Nadu (324) Andhra Pradesh (97) and Karnataka (92).
--
