[7] India - New Delhi
Date: 2 Nov 2006
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Daily News & Analysis, Mumbai,India, 2 Nov 2006 [edited]
<http://www.dnaindia.com/report.asp?NewsID=1061706>

Sixty-seven fresh cases of dengue were registered in hospitals across
the capital, taking the total number of patients to 2775. The
capital, where 62 people have died this year due to the viral
[infection], did not report any dengue deaths on Thursday.
Twenty-five fresh cases of the mosquito-borne disease were reported
at the AIIMS [All India Institute of Medical Sciences - Mod.TY],
where 144 patients have been receiving treatment for the viral
[infection]. The AIIMS has discharged 34 dengue patients following
their recovery from the illness.
--
